    "body": "#### ODK Collect version\r\nv2023.2 Beta 3\r\n#### Android version\r\n10, 13\r\n#### Device used\r\nRedmi 9T, Pixel 6a\r\n#### Problem description\r\nAfter, clicking on the Sent button in main menu and then opening a form with background recording, the recording becomes active despite no Form in Draft or Ready to sent.  \r\n#### Steps to reproduce the problem\r\nThere are two ways to reproduce the issue: \r\n\r\n**First way:** \r\n1. Have at least one Form with Background Audio Recording in Sent tab\r\n2. Navigate to Sent tab and view any Form with background recording;\r\n3. Click on Exit button;\r\n4. Navigate to Start new form;\r\n5. Open any form;\r\n6. Click Stop button in the recording bar;\r\n7. App will crash\r\n\r\n**Second way:**\r\n1. Open a form with background Recording;\r\n2. Go to the end and Send form;\r\n3. Click View form Snackbar;\r\n4. Repeat steps 3-6 from First way\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n1. Background recording should not start after viewing sent form;\r\n2. Recording bar should not be visible in forms without recording available\r\n#### Other information \r\nForm I used:\r\n[AuditTestLocationBackgroundAudiowithoutaudioqualityset2.xml.txt](https://github.com/getodk/collect/files/11879793/AuditTestLocationBackgroundAudiowithoutaudioqualityset2.xml.txt)\r\n\r\nVideo: \r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/getodk/collect/assets/85225519/879e7d1e-794c-431e-a306-2b4b8492c9b0\r\n\r\nError Message after crash:\r\n![Screenshot_20230627-095543](https://github.com/getodk/collect/assets/85225519/d5b9928e-9238-4304-b4e8-015148a7329d)\r\n\r\n\r\n",
